# Paths Semgrep skips. Mirrors .gitignore where useful + adds vendored
# / generated paths that semgrep can otherwise spend minutes scanning.

# Vendor / build output
node_modules/
.venv/
dist/
build/
.next/
.parcel-cache/

# Generated
*.lock
uv.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml
package-lock.json

# Test fixtures + replay caches (no production code)
**/.langchain_cache.json
**/test/fixtures/

# Test-scaffolding layer — excluded from production wheels (see
# apps/backend/pyproject.toml [tool.hatch.build.targets.wheel]) and gated by
# `is_dev_env()` at the HTTP boundary. Test helpers legitimately use patterns
# (DB TRUNCATE, hardcoded fake secrets) that Semgrep flags as risky in
# production code.
**/app/testing/

# Test files themselves (real code is covered)
**/test/test_*.py

# Plan docs (Markdown, but semgrep can pattern-match against text too)
plan/

# Docker context files
docker/

# Migrations — autogenerated alembic output
**/alembic/versions/
